&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Cloudflare&#39;s Legal Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cloudflare Legal team is at the forefront of some of the most complex and novel legal issues in technology today. You will be directly supporting our &lt;strong&gt;Policy&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Public Sector Legal&lt;/strong&gt; teams. These teams work collaboratively to navigate the rapidly evolving regulatory landscape, ensure Cloudflare’s compliance with stringent government standards (like FedRAMP and StateRAMP), and advocate for policies that promote a secure, privacy-respecting, and innovative Internet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Summer Legal Intern, you will dive headfirst into the intersection of law, policy, and cutting-edge technology. With a specific emphasis on the rapidly shifting AI and cybersecurity environments in North America, your day-to-day responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Policy &amp;amp; Compliance Research:&lt;/strong&gt; Track and analyze emerging artificial intelligence legislation and frameworks across North America, including US federal initiatives (e.g., Executive Orders, NIST AI RMF), state-level AI regulations (e.g., California, Colorado), and Canada’s Artificial Intelligence and Data Act (AIDA).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cybersecurity Regulatory Tracking:&lt;/strong&gt; Monitor updates to cybersecurity mandates such as CISA’s Secure by Design guidelines, SEC incident reporting rules, and critical infrastructure protection frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Public Sector Enablement:&lt;/strong&gt; Assist the Public Sector legal team in reviewing and updating compliance materials related to FedRAMP, StateRAMP, and IRAP requirements, helping to accelerate our mission to secure government entities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drafting &amp;amp; Advocacy:&lt;/strong&gt; Draft legal memos, policy briefs, and internal guidance documents outlining how new North American tech regulations impact Cloudflare’s product roadmap, including our AI Gateway and zero-trust security services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Examples of desirable skills, knowledge and experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt; Currently enrolled as a 1L or 2L in an ABA-accredited law school, with an anticipated graduation date of 2027 or 2028.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tech-Forward Mindset:&lt;/strong&gt; A strong demonstrated interest in technology law, public policy, cybersecurity, and artificial intelligence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analytical Rigor:&lt;/strong&gt; Excellent legal research and writing skills, with the ability to distill dense regulatory text into clear, business-friendly advice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initiative:&lt;/strong&gt; A self-starter mentality. You are comfortable navigating ambiguity and thrive in a fast-paced, highly collaborative environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to commit to a minimum 12 week summer internship.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In the office 3-5 days a week in the Washington D.C. office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bonus Points if you have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience (internships, clinics, or pre-law career) in government, a public policy organization, or a technology company&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Cloudflare’s products, cloud computing infrastructure, and the general mechanics of how the Internet works.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coursework or certifications in data privacy (CIPP/US), cybersecurity law, or national security law.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
